Gungho, you forget that you have to move out from the pet's melee range and re-root it before you can blast again. A chrystallized pumice also works well to keep pet free, since it has no recast time.<br>
<br>
If the necro is using a 53 pet (appx 1300 hps) or 56 pet (appx 1500 hps), I would recommend that a wizzie simply kills the pet before working the necro. Spell nerf doesn't apply to attacks against pets, so they can be instakilled with a well-placed sunstrike. The level 59 pet has more hps though (like 2300). Also keep in mind that a de-agroed pet regens hps quite quickly (maybe 40-50 hps / tick). I try to back off my pet as often I can in battle, to save its health (important since every tank I fight has a coldain ring dmg shield which hurts the pet a bit). <br>
<br>
I might add that, when I have a pet with SoW, haste and resist magic, the pet alone has a good chance of turning wizzies or petless mages / necros into dogmeat. <br>
